            <fullName>Book_Appointment_Nav_179ak000002oR1c</fullName>
            <description>Creates the ServiceAppointment after the user picks a slot. Returns appointmentNumber, scheduled start/end UTC ISO, optional time zone, and confirmation message. Pass patientLookupEmail as a plain email string only (e.g. priya.sharma@example.com). patientLookupEmail MUST be a simple string literal—never a JSON object and never include recipientId, subject, body, to, or cc. Do not ask the patient for a Salesforce Account or Contact Id. Work Type Id may be omitted for default new consult. First-time patients: if this action returns an error stating no matching patient was found for the email, call Register Patient Nav (collecting first name, last name, email, and explicit consentToContact=true) and then retry Book Appointment with the same email.</description>
            <developerName>Book_Appointment_Nav_179ak000002oR1c</developerName>
            <invocationTarget>OncoSchedulingBook</invocationTarget>
            <invocationTargetType>apex</invocationTargetType>
            <isConfirmationRequired>false</isConfirmationRequired>
            <isIncludeInProgressIndicator>true</isIncludeInProgressIndicator>
            <localDeveloperName>Book_Appointment_Nav</localDeveloperName>
            <masterLabel>Book Appointment</masterLabel>
            <progressIndicatorMessage>Finalizing your oncology consultation...</progressIndicatorMessage>
        </localActions>
        <localActions>
            <fullName>Onco_Get_Slots_Nav_179ak000002oR1b</fullName>
            <description>Returns candidate appointment times. REQUIRED INPUTS: HealthcareFacility Id AND either HealthcareProvider Id or CareSpecialty Id. You MUST acquire these Ids by calling prerequisite tools first—do NOT guess, do NOT re-use Ids from an earlier turn, do NOT make up Ids. PREREQUISITE CHAIN for &quot;slots for &lt;specialty&gt; in &lt;city&gt;&quot; (department-first): (1) call Find Cancer Care Facilities with the city to get a HealthcareFacility Id from plannerReferenceText, (2) call Search Oncology Specialties with the specialty name to get a CareSpecialty Id from plannerReferenceText, (3) then call this action with both Ids. PREREQUISITE CHAIN for &quot;slots with Dr. X in &lt;city&gt;&quot; (named doctor): (1) call Find Cancer Care Facilities with the city to get a HealthcareFacility Id, (2) call Find Oncology Providers with the doctor name to get a HealthcareProvider Id, (3) then call this action with both Ids. Work Type Id may be omitted (defaults to Onco New Consult). Returns slotsText for the patient and per-slot HealthcareProvider Ids in plannerReferenceText for Book. Do not describe availability without running this action after the prerequisites.</description>
            <developerName>Onco_Get_Slots_Nav_179ak000002oR1b</developerName>
            <invocationTarget>OncoSchedulingSlotsAgent</invocationTarget>
            <invocationTargetType>apex</invocationTargetType>
            <isConfirmationRequired>false</isConfirmationRequired>
            <isIncludeInProgressIndicator>true</isIncludeInProgressIndicator>
            <localDeveloperName>Onco_Get_Slots_Nav</localDeveloperName>
            <masterLabel>Get Available Appointment Slots</masterLabel>
            <progressIndicatorMessage>Computing slots...</progressIndicatorMessage>
        </localActions>
        <localActions>
            <fullName>Onco_Find_Providers_Nav_179ak000002oR1a</fullName>
            <description>Finds oncology doctors. ALWAYS call this tool when the user asks any of: &quot;find a doctor&quot;, &quot;who treats &lt;cancer&gt;&quot;, &quot;oncologist at &lt;hospital&gt;&quot;, &quot;list &lt;specialty&gt; doctors in &lt;city&gt;&quot;, or mentions a doctor by name (e.g. &quot;Dr. Arjun Mehta&quot;, &quot;book with Dr. Priyanka Nair&quot;). Do not say there are no doctors without running this tool. Pass any of: city, specialty text, facility name substring, or provider name substring from the user message. Returns patient-safe names in providersText and HealthcareProvider Ids in plannerReferenceText for Get Slots and Book.</description>
            <developerName>Onco_Find_Providers_Nav_179ak000002oR1a</developerName>
            <invocationTarget>OncoDiscoveryProvidersAgent</invocationTarget>
            <invocationTargetType>apex</invocationTargetType>
            <isConfirmationRequired>false</isConfirmationRequired>
