        <localActions>
            <fullName>Onco_List_My_Appointments_Nav_179ak000002oR1f</fullName>
            <description>Lists a patient&apos;s Onco Global visits (past and upcoming) from Health Cloud. ALWAYS call this tool fresh whenever the user asks about their appointments, even if you already answered a similar question earlier in this conversation. Never answer appointment questions from prior-turn memory—re-invoke the tool every time. Triggers: &quot;list my appointments&quot;, &quot;show me my appointments&quot;, &quot;what appointments do I have&quot;, &quot;when is my next visit&quot;, &quot;all my bookings&quot;, &quot;include cancelled&quot;, &quot;past and upcoming&quot;, &quot;show everything&quot;, &quot;also show past&quot;. Pass patientLookupEmail as the user&apos;s plain email address string verbatim (for example priya.sharma@example.com); never wrap it in a JSON object. Set includePast=true whenever the user mentions past, completed, cancelled, history, all, everything, or &quot;past and upcoming&quot;; set includePast=false only when the user explicitly says &quot;only upcoming&quot; or &quot;next&quot;. Returns patient-safe appointment numbers (e.g. SA-0017), start times, status, visit type, and territory in appointmentsText. Never a Salesforce Account Id.</description>
            <developerName>Onco_List_My_Appointments_Nav_179ak000002oR1f</developerName>
            <invocationTarget>OncoListAppointmentsAgent</invocationTarget>
            <invocationTargetType>apex</invocationTargetType>
